this is for ubuntu 

in home directory open file .profile or .bashrc (show hidden files if you're using the gui)

in the end of the file add PATH="$PATH:insert the path you want to add here"

save and logout to apply changes

export PATH="$PATH:/home/ahmed/installations/JCD/java_card_devkit_tools-bin-v24/bin"
export JC_HOME="/home/ahmed/installations/JCD/java_card_devkit_tools-bin-v24/"

changes can be temporarily applied for a single terminal session by using source .profile (that is assuming you're in your home/yourName (~) directory
